      "unix.desc": "A free online tool to convert Unix timestamps to human-readable dates and vice versa.",
      "unix.longDesc.title": "About Unix Timestamp Converter",
      "unix.longDesc.p1": "This tool is a free online **Unix Timestamp Converter** that translates Unix timestamps (the time elapsed since January 1, 1970 UTC in seconds or milliseconds) into human-readable dates and times, or vice versa.",
      "unix.longDesc.p2": "It supports not only single conversions but also a Batch Mode to process multiple timestamps or dates at once, which is highly useful for developers and system administrators analyzing large volumes of log data. The converted results are provided in detail as local time, UTC, ISO 8601 format, and relative time (e.g., '2 hours ago'), and includes quick action features to instantly copy the current time.",
      "unix.longDesc.p3": "All time conversion operations are processed instantly in your browser, so you can get results quickly and securely without server communication delays. Maximize your work efficiency by utilizing the Unix Timestamp Converter for various tasks such as server log analysis, database time data verification, and API development.",
